assessment_details.task_description:
This assignment provides students with an opportunity to demonstrate their understanding developed in the subject to the practical analysis and demonstration of an employee and/or organisational development strategy or intervention.

In groups, ideally of 3-5, students will research and present a strategy of intervention, suitable for a real-life organisation. Students are not to examine a particular organisation as such: they are simply to take a real-life focus when researching and presenting this particular strategy or intervention.

This group assessment has three components: a written component (20%), a peer assessment component (5%) and a presentation component (5%). The presentation component can be submitted on the subject Blackboard or on a USB. Students are not expected to develop a video or DVD as such: it is simply to be an audio-visual record of 5 minutes in length, based upon your written paper.

Students may chose any relevant topic within this subject, for possible application for any private, public or not-for-profit organisation, based in Australia or outside Australia. The paper would be based upon that investigation. The presentation itself would be a summary or a particular part of that paper, as foor example:

the beginning of a structured experience/management game to foster team building;

the end of a training session to middle managers on how to foster employee voice;

the beginning of a meeting with an external consultant on your organisation's needs and your desired outcomes from their consultancy;

the beginning of a problem-solving workshop using either process consultation or appreciative enquiry;

the summary of a presentation to the executive team on why human metrics is important to their enterprise.
